<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I want to select the following in the following column order:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$select = $db-&gt;select()
    -&gt;from(array('a' =&gt; $config-&gt;$table), array('a.code', 'b.company', 'a.sale_date'))
    -&gt;joinLeft(array('b' =&gt; $config-&gt;db_tbl_finances_debtors),
        'a.debtor_id = b.debtor_id', array())
    -&gt;order('a.code DESC');
</code></pre>

<p>When the SQL is generated I get this:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
SELECT
    `a`.`code`,
    `a`.`sale_date`,
    `b`.`company`
FROM `finances_invoices` AS `a`
  LEFT JOIN `finances_debtors` AS `b` ON a.debtor_id = b.debtor_id 
ORDER BY
    `a`.`code` DESC
</code></pre>

<p>It has reordered the Columns!!</p>

<p>How do I stop this doing this behaviour.</p>

